of which are well formed and healthy
Almost sinking under the heat of -
the freshness of the air which we here
experienced seemed a blessing sent from
heaven and every object that we beheld
appeared warmed with beauty and filled with
life -
The summits of Volcanic mountains
when elevated to any considerable height or
after having felt the effects of an eruption
present a striking contrast when examined
in the same vie w with the lower regions -

[page]20|MS-DAVY-11705-000-00020|dnp17e16pp|95148892[/page]
Black and rugged and barren if not
